The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Shrachi set to hunt for cash

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Todi in Calcutta on Tuesday. A Telegraph picture

 Calcutta, Jan. 31: Shrachi Infrastructure Finance Ltd, formerly Shrachi Securities, is planning to raise Rs 15-20 crore to meet its working capital requirements. The company is likely to make a preferential allotment to raise the cash, leading an equity dilution of 10-15 per cent.

 Managing director Ravi Todi said the capital would be raised during this quarter.

 Cash is the raw material for us. To support business growth plans, we need fresh resources, Todi told reporters.

 The company recently made a preferential allotment of warrants to promoters group at Rs 53 (with a premium of Rs 43) per share.

 Going forward this year, it intends to focus on the construction equipment and second-hand vehicle lending.

 During the third quarter, the company clocked a 32 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 2.38 crore compared with Rs 1.80 crore last fiscal. Total income touched Rs 7.89 crore (Rs 6.46 crore).

 The company had appointed KPMG to study its business model and suggest areas of growth. It is studying the draft report given by KPMG.

 Magma Leasing

 Magma Leasing Ltd, has reported a 105 per cent growth in net profit at Rs 6.65 crore for the third quarter ended December against Rs 3.24 crore in the year-ago period.

 Managing director Sanjay Chamria said the company has achieved a 59 per cent growth in business disbursals during the quarter against only 27 per cent achieved in the first two quarters. 




